WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.335 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:02.335 --> 00:00:04.670 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.670 --> 00:00:07.590 align:middle line:90%
[OTHERWORLDLY MUSIC]

00:00:07.590 --> 00:00:37.470 align:middle line:90%


00:00:37.470 --> 00:00:40.670 align:middle line:90%
[STIRRING MUSIC]

00:00:40.670 --> 00:00:41.470 align:middle line:90%


00:00:41.470 --> 00:00:45.760 align:middle line:84%
>> Throughout time,
there are stories told.

00:00:45.760 --> 00:00:49.690 align:middle line:84%
Some encounters are more
mysterious than others,

00:00:49.690 --> 00:00:53.220 align:middle line:84%
mystical beings from
mermaids to giants.

00:00:53.220 --> 00:00:56.490 align:middle line:90%


00:00:56.490 --> 00:01:03.060 align:middle line:84%
There are clues throughout
history that cannot be ignored.

00:01:03.060 --> 00:01:05.880 align:middle line:84%
Often, there is
proof that confirms

00:01:05.880 --> 00:01:09.240 align:middle line:84%
the presence of these
beings, and sometimes there

00:01:09.240 --> 00:01:15.790 align:middle line:84%
is only folklore, legend,
and myth, mystical beings

00:01:15.790 --> 00:01:17.245 align:middle line:90%
from the other side.

00:01:17.245 --> 00:01:31.340 align:middle line:90%


00:01:31.340 --> 00:01:35.560 align:middle line:84%
>> So if you ask me the question
if I believe in the water

00:01:35.560 --> 00:01:42.490 align:middle line:84%
families, I believe in it
because the elderly people--

00:01:42.490 --> 00:01:45.970 align:middle line:84%
their stories are so
real and so realistic.

00:01:45.970 --> 00:01:48.370 align:middle line:84%
And we'll listen
to their stories

00:01:48.370 --> 00:01:51.760 align:middle line:90%
from generation to generation.

00:01:51.760 --> 00:01:55.930 align:middle line:84%
And today, I'm in the front
line of the new generation,

00:01:55.930 --> 00:01:59.020 align:middle line:84%
and I must also
tell those stories

00:01:59.020 --> 00:02:02.410 align:middle line:84%
to the people in
the new generations

00:02:02.410 --> 00:02:07.309 align:middle line:84%
because it comes from the
heart of the people that

00:02:07.309 --> 00:02:08.559 align:middle line:90%
used to tell us those stories.

00:02:08.559 --> 00:02:32.510 align:middle line:90%


00:02:32.510 --> 00:02:35.790 align:middle line:84%
>> Me and my family
moved here in 2013.

00:02:35.790 --> 00:02:38.200 align:middle line:10%
The name Shadowlands
basically was

00:02:38.200 --> 00:02:42.760 align:middle line:10%
used by the previous owner,
very good friends of ours.

00:02:42.760 --> 00:02:46.960 align:middle line:10%
He sort of dreamed of
retiring on the farm and pity

00:02:46.960 --> 00:02:49.630 align:middle line:10%
that, within a couple of
months after moving here,

00:02:49.630 --> 00:02:50.530 align:middle line:10%
he got cancer.

00:02:50.530 --> 00:02:52.600 align:middle line:10%
And then he died
in the farm here.

00:02:52.600 --> 00:02:55.450 align:middle line:10%
The actual name
Shadowlands comes

00:02:55.450 --> 00:02:58.383 align:middle line:10%
from where we are at
the moment in my life

00:02:58.383 --> 00:03:00.550 align:middle line:10%
and where the previous owner
were in the shadowlands

00:03:00.550 --> 00:03:01.350 align:middle line:10%
of our lives.

00:03:01.350 --> 00:03:03.940 align:middle line:10%
We are towards the
end of our life.

00:03:03.940 --> 00:03:06.160 align:middle line:10%
When we arrived here,
we heard all kinds

00:03:06.160 --> 00:03:08.950 align:middle line:10%
of stories about the
waterhole on the farm,

00:03:08.950 --> 00:03:11.470 align:middle line:10%
some horrible stories and
some intriguing stories.

00:03:11.470 --> 00:03:14.680 align:middle line:10%
The waterhole behind
you is intriguing.

00:03:14.680 --> 00:03:17.890 align:middle line:10%
We are in the middle of the
worst drought in human history.

00:03:17.890 --> 00:03:21.070 align:middle line:10%
It's now been 6 and 1/2 years
with no rain, with no water,

00:03:21.070 --> 00:03:22.810 align:middle line:10%
no water flow in
the Kammanassie.

00:03:22.810 --> 00:03:26.530 align:middle line:10%
When we arrived, we heard about
the story about the waterhole

00:03:26.530 --> 00:03:29.320 align:middle line:10%
being part of the culture
of the Khoisan people

00:03:29.320 --> 00:03:31.660 align:middle line:10%
and didn't really notice it.

00:03:31.660 --> 00:03:34.480 align:middle line:10%
And when the drought hit and
all the water disappears,

00:03:34.480 --> 00:03:36.490 align:middle line:10%
it is so dry that
even the baboons

00:03:36.490 --> 00:03:37.720 align:middle line:10%
are dying at the moment.

00:03:37.720 --> 00:03:40.510 align:middle line:10%
And still, there is water
in this hole behind me.

00:03:40.510 --> 00:03:42.430 align:middle line:10%
In the cave on the
top of the mountain

00:03:42.430 --> 00:03:44.470 align:middle line:10%
there, there's always
been water dripping.

00:03:44.470 --> 00:03:46.420 align:middle line:10%
And again, the San
people must have

00:03:46.420 --> 00:03:48.760 align:middle line:10%
known this is a place where
they can come and fill

00:03:48.760 --> 00:03:51.590 align:middle line:10%
their water bottles or whatever,
the eggs, whatever they used.

00:03:51.590 --> 00:03:54.490 align:middle line:10%
And as I said, now, after
almost eight years now,

00:03:54.490 --> 00:03:58.540 align:middle line:10%
the waterhole is just as full
as has been eight years ago.

00:03:58.540 --> 00:04:01.420 align:middle line:84%
>> In many cultural
groups across Africa,

00:04:01.420 --> 00:04:04.070 align:middle line:90%
water and rain law is important.

00:04:04.070 --> 00:04:06.620 align:middle line:84%
Indigenous tribes,
like the Attaquas,

00:04:06.620 --> 00:04:09.320 align:middle line:84%
have generations
thick with stories

00:04:09.320 --> 00:04:13.100 align:middle line:84%
relating to water,
rich folklore and tales

00:04:13.100 --> 00:04:16.070 align:middle line:84%
about merbeings
and water families.

00:04:16.070 --> 00:04:21.500 align:middle line:84%
250 million years ago, the
area was completely underwater.

00:04:21.500 --> 00:04:24.410 align:middle line:84%
And when it receded,
a sacred place

00:04:24.410 --> 00:04:28.010 align:middle line:84%
was left behind, a
valley with water holes

00:04:28.010 --> 00:04:31.760 align:middle line:84%
where mountain springs trickle
and mermaids are believed

00:04:31.760 --> 00:04:33.710 align:middle line:90%
to have sought sanctuary.

00:04:33.710 --> 00:04:38.660 align:middle line:84%
One of these water holes is
right here at Shadowlands.

00:04:38.660 --> 00:04:42.140 align:middle line:10%
>> I met Poem Mooney, and
Poem Mooney is the chief

00:04:42.140 --> 00:04:46.760 align:middle line:10%
of the Attaquas tribal
unit in this area.

00:04:46.760 --> 00:04:49.350 align:middle line:10%
And to tell you how
we met is difficult.

00:04:49.350 --> 00:04:50.390 align:middle line:10%
I can't really remember.

00:04:50.390 --> 00:04:52.932 align:middle line:10%
But over nine years now, we've
been really been good friends.

00:04:52.932 --> 00:04:56.690 align:middle line:10%
And although we've got
vast different backgrounds

00:04:56.690 --> 00:04:59.660 align:middle line:10%
and cultures, we've got one
thing in common and our bond

00:04:59.660 --> 00:05:01.190 align:middle line:10%
and that is to tell stories.

00:05:01.190 --> 00:05:02.840 align:middle line:10%
And life is about
telling stories.

00:05:02.840 --> 00:05:06.380 align:middle line:10%
That's how people in the past
taught their children, and we--

00:05:06.380 --> 00:05:08.920 align:middle line:10%
I love telling stories.

00:05:08.920 --> 00:05:11.150 align:middle line:10%
I, in the beginning,
didn't know he was a chief.

00:05:11.150 --> 00:05:13.160 align:middle line:10%
I just know him as
a good storyteller

00:05:13.160 --> 00:05:15.660 align:middle line:10%
and as a person that's
passionate for his tribe

00:05:15.660 --> 00:05:16.550 align:middle line:10%
and for his past.

00:05:16.550 --> 00:05:18.590 align:middle line:10%
The San people,
especially the Attaquas,

00:05:18.590 --> 00:05:20.390 align:middle line:10%
dream about the
cultural center on this

00:05:20.390 --> 00:05:22.760 align:middle line:10%
from, a place where
they can nurture

00:05:22.760 --> 00:05:25.340 align:middle line:10%
their beliefs and their past.

00:05:25.340 --> 00:05:29.300 align:middle line:84%
>> Wisdom culture and history
are passed down through

00:05:29.300 --> 00:05:33.980 align:middle line:84%
stories, a map to one's past
and one's future beliefs.

00:05:33.980 --> 00:05:38.540 align:middle line:84%
Merbeings and water families
are part of this oral history.

00:05:38.540 --> 00:05:42.020 align:middle line:84%
They have existed in
legends, myth, and folklore

00:05:42.020 --> 00:05:43.280 align:middle line:90%
for centuries.

00:05:43.280 --> 00:05:44.720 align:middle line:90%
They are sacred.

00:05:44.720 --> 00:05:48.950 align:middle line:84%
Coming up next, we meet Poem
Mooney, an Attaqua chief

00:05:48.950 --> 00:05:51.230 align:middle line:84%
and storyteller,
who can tell you

00:05:51.230 --> 00:05:55.820 align:middle line:84%
many tales of mermaids in the
area surrounding Shadowlands.

00:05:55.820 --> 00:05:59.720 align:middle line:84%
Join us as we journey with
him to the other side.

00:05:59.720 --> 00:06:01.610 align:middle line:90%
[CALM MUSIC]

00:06:01.610 --> 00:06:03.470 align:middle line:90%
>> My name is Poem Mooney.

00:06:03.470 --> 00:06:05.210 align:middle line:90%
Poem is only a nickname.

00:06:05.210 --> 00:06:11.420 align:middle line:84%
My actual name is Skerp
Petrus Jacobus Mooney.

00:06:11.420 --> 00:06:15.290 align:middle line:84%
And I'm the chief
of the Attaquas.

00:06:15.290 --> 00:06:18.450 align:middle line:84%
the Attaquas Khoisan people
that live between the Outeniqua

00:06:18.450 --> 00:06:20.310 align:middle line:90%
and the Swartberg Mountains.

00:06:20.310 --> 00:06:25.470 align:middle line:84%
I'm sitting on Shadowlands,
the farm of Anton Roetz.

00:06:25.470 --> 00:06:29.520 align:middle line:84%
I usually come here
before because I'm

00:06:29.520 --> 00:06:33.270 align:middle line:84%
interested in the
waterhole on the farm.

00:06:33.270 --> 00:06:36.870 align:middle line:84%
Because in that waterhole,
there lives a mermaid.

00:06:36.870 --> 00:06:42.705 align:middle line:90%


00:06:42.705 --> 00:06:45.270 align:middle line:90%
I don't like the word "mermaid".

00:06:45.270 --> 00:06:50.310 align:middle line:90%
It sounds too English.

00:06:50.310 --> 00:06:51.540 align:middle line:90%
She's a water--

00:06:51.540 --> 00:06:53.400 align:middle line:90%
[SPEAKING AFRIKAANS]

00:06:53.400 --> 00:06:55.620 align:middle line:84%
And she was happy
with that name.

00:06:55.620 --> 00:06:59.670 align:middle line:84%
She swam from the one
waterhole in the Kammanassie

00:06:59.670 --> 00:07:04.740 align:middle line:84%
up to the waterhole at
Shadowlands to Calitzdorp.

00:07:04.740 --> 00:07:08.700 align:middle line:84%
Around every waterhole, there
are thousands and thousands

00:07:08.700 --> 00:07:12.270 align:middle line:90%
of stories about the mermaid.

00:07:12.270 --> 00:07:14.820 align:middle line:84%
The other day, one of
my friends asked me,

00:07:14.820 --> 00:07:16.350 align:middle line:90%
"but where is she now?"

00:07:16.350 --> 00:07:18.340 align:middle line:90%
We haven't seen her.

00:07:18.340 --> 00:07:19.830 align:middle line:90%
He said "you won't see her".

00:07:19.830 --> 00:07:25.890 align:middle line:84%
Because of the people
that come to live here,

00:07:25.890 --> 00:07:30.600 align:middle line:84%
there was such a lot of
noise because the farms

00:07:30.600 --> 00:07:35.160 align:middle line:84%
get nearer and nearer to
the waterhole, the tractors

00:07:35.160 --> 00:07:41.710 align:middle line:84%
and the lorries and the sound
of children and of people.

00:07:41.710 --> 00:07:45.070 align:middle line:90%
It scared them so much.

00:07:45.070 --> 00:07:50.620 align:middle line:84%
And over the years, she only
comes out for a little while.

00:07:50.620 --> 00:07:53.020 align:middle line:84%
And then she goes
back into the water.

00:07:53.020 --> 00:07:57.640 align:middle line:84%
And then, all of a
sudden, she disappeared.

00:07:57.640 --> 00:08:00.520 align:middle line:84%
And after we do a
thorough research,

00:08:00.520 --> 00:08:02.050 align:middle line:90%
we went to the waterhole.

00:08:02.050 --> 00:08:06.340 align:middle line:84%
And I can show you
the portal where

00:08:06.340 --> 00:08:11.920 align:middle line:84%
she went through from this
world into another world.

00:08:11.920 --> 00:08:16.120 align:middle line:84%
And you know what
that means to me?

00:08:16.120 --> 00:08:22.160 align:middle line:84%
We are on this Earth
only for a time.

00:08:22.160 --> 00:08:28.330 align:middle line:84%
And then after that, we
will also go from this world

00:08:28.330 --> 00:08:30.010 align:middle line:90%
to another world.

00:08:30.010 --> 00:08:32.799 align:middle line:84%
We want to bring
her back by telling

00:08:32.799 --> 00:08:36.230 align:middle line:84%
all the wonderful stories
about the mermaid of the Little

00:08:36.230 --> 00:08:37.030 align:middle line:90%
Karoo.

00:08:37.030 --> 00:08:41.010 align:middle line:90%
[TRIBAL MUSIC]

00:08:41.010 --> 00:08:44.760 align:middle line:84%
>> For tribes like the
Attaqua, word is bond,

00:08:44.760 --> 00:08:50.970 align:middle line:84%
whispers spoken around campfires
by elders stories are sacred

00:08:50.970 --> 00:08:52.830 align:middle line:90%
and hold immense weight.

00:08:52.830 --> 00:08:57.490 align:middle line:90%


00:08:57.490 --> 00:09:02.660 align:middle line:84%
>> While we are here, I
will read the poem to you.

00:09:02.660 --> 00:09:04.720 align:middle line:10%
[SPEAKING AFRIKAANS]

00:09:04.720 --> 00:12:11.930 align:middle line:90%


00:12:11.930 --> 00:12:15.272 align:middle line:90%
[STIRRING MUSIC]

00:12:15.272 --> 00:12:27.080 align:middle line:90%


00:12:27.080 --> 00:12:31.130 align:middle line:84%
>> This is the Kammanassie
River that goes past us.

00:12:31.130 --> 00:12:35.240 align:middle line:84%
The whole of the bottom there
is a portal Poem talks about,

00:12:35.240 --> 00:12:37.860 align:middle line:84%
and he will tell you the
story about the portal.

00:12:37.860 --> 00:12:41.420 align:middle line:84%
And I think, as we're
going to walk closer there,

00:12:41.420 --> 00:12:45.680 align:middle line:84%
everyone will know and will
actually feel the presence

00:12:45.680 --> 00:12:46.850 align:middle line:90%
around this waterhole.

00:12:46.850 --> 00:12:49.340 align:middle line:90%
There is something there.

00:12:49.340 --> 00:12:52.380 align:middle line:84%
At the moment, we've
got all this water.

00:12:52.380 --> 00:12:55.850 align:middle line:84%
It's a massive piece of water
layer, and it's not usable.

00:12:55.850 --> 00:12:59.600 align:middle line:84%
It is completely,
completely salty.

00:12:59.600 --> 00:13:01.560 align:middle line:84%
It's gone salty
after eight years.

00:13:01.560 --> 00:13:04.310 align:middle line:84%
So again, the
Indigenous people here

00:13:04.310 --> 00:13:07.220 align:middle line:84%
would have known about that
hole in the mountain there.

00:13:07.220 --> 00:13:09.740 align:middle line:84%
Because even now,
you can go in there.

00:13:09.740 --> 00:13:12.560 align:middle line:84%
There's still green algae in
there, and that is fresh water.

00:13:12.560 --> 00:13:14.450 align:middle line:84%
That is not the
salty water bottom.

00:13:14.450 --> 00:13:15.950 align:middle line:84%
That hole on the
top there must have

00:13:15.950 --> 00:13:19.770 align:middle line:84%
been a watering hole for many,
many, many, many thousands

00:13:19.770 --> 00:13:20.570 align:middle line:90%
of years.

00:13:20.570 --> 00:13:22.452 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, it was like a fountain.

00:13:22.452 --> 00:13:23.660 align:middle line:90%
>> It's like a fountain, yes.

00:13:23.660 --> 00:13:25.320 align:middle line:90%
>> It was like a fountain.

00:13:25.320 --> 00:13:26.250 align:middle line:90%
That was running.

00:13:26.250 --> 00:13:28.470 align:middle line:84%
>> And that's basically
where-- the top hole--

00:13:28.470 --> 00:13:31.440 align:middle line:84%
if you look at the top hole,
which is now the fountain,

00:13:31.440 --> 00:13:33.240 align:middle line:84%
the bottom hole at
the bottom there--

00:13:33.240 --> 00:13:35.685 align:middle line:84%
that is more the portal
Poem will tell you about.

00:13:35.685 --> 00:13:38.250 align:middle line:84%
And the top hole was
the old watering hole

00:13:38.250 --> 00:13:39.960 align:middle line:84%
for all the San
people, basically.

00:13:39.960 --> 00:14:00.150 align:middle line:90%


00:14:00.150 --> 00:14:05.130 align:middle line:10%
>> There's a lot of stories
that hides in the cliffs

00:14:05.130 --> 00:14:10.125 align:middle line:10%
and the mountains
[SPEAKING AFRIKAANS]

00:14:10.125 --> 00:14:11.310 align:middle line:90%


00:14:11.310 --> 00:14:12.840 align:middle line:90%
There's lots of stories.

00:14:12.840 --> 00:14:15.150 align:middle line:84%
>> Poem, can I ask you to
tell them the story about

00:14:15.150 --> 00:14:16.750 align:middle line:90%
[AFRIKAANS]?

00:14:16.750 --> 00:14:17.700 align:middle line:90%
>> Ya.

00:14:17.700 --> 00:14:19.530 align:middle line:10%
[SPEAKING AFRIKAANS]

00:14:19.530 --> 00:15:20.670 align:middle line:90%


00:15:20.670 --> 00:15:23.490 align:middle line:84%
>> Folklore has
existed for centuries,

00:15:23.490 --> 00:15:26.310 align:middle line:84%
from portals to
other dimensions,

00:15:26.310 --> 00:15:29.130 align:middle line:84%
shamans who would
call upon the rains,

00:15:29.130 --> 00:15:32.910 align:middle line:84%
fairies who turn fish into
rocks, and a water mead,

00:15:32.910 --> 00:15:35.070 align:middle line:90%
half-woman, half-fish.

00:15:35.070 --> 00:15:40.080 align:middle line:84%
What if there was more than just
stories, actual proof carved

00:15:40.080 --> 00:15:42.570 align:middle line:90%
into walls from years past?

00:15:42.570 --> 00:15:45.510 align:middle line:84%
Coming up next, we
meet Jaralow, who

00:15:45.510 --> 00:15:49.650 align:middle line:84%
reveals a hidden cave with
ancient paintings of mermaids.

00:15:49.650 --> 00:15:53.280 align:middle line:84%
Join us as we journey with
him to the other side.

00:15:53.280 --> 00:15:56.658 align:middle line:90%
[LIVELY MUSIC]

00:15:56.658 --> 00:16:29.710 align:middle line:90%


00:16:29.710 --> 00:16:32.280 align:middle line:84%
>> Now we arrive at the
place where you can watch

00:16:32.280 --> 00:16:34.560 align:middle line:90%
the mermaid.

00:16:34.560 --> 00:16:39.750 align:middle line:84%
You are well-known to this
area, so you can show them

00:16:39.750 --> 00:16:42.420 align:middle line:90%
the mermaid rock art.

00:16:42.420 --> 00:16:46.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Yes, we have found
it a few years ago.

00:16:46.000 --> 00:16:49.830 align:middle line:84%
So we used to come and
show our guests this one,

00:16:49.830 --> 00:16:54.480 align:middle line:84%
but we want to keep it a secret
because lots of people-- they

00:16:54.480 --> 00:16:57.420 align:middle line:90%
destroy these kind of history.

00:16:57.420 --> 00:17:00.660 align:middle line:84%
I know something about
that dot paintings.

00:17:00.660 --> 00:17:06.720 align:middle line:84%
That dot paintings is like,
when one group are staying here,

00:17:06.720 --> 00:17:09.420 align:middle line:84%
so they leave a message
for the next group that

00:17:09.420 --> 00:17:12.450 align:middle line:84%
is coming to tell
them that they don't

00:17:12.450 --> 00:17:14.740 align:middle line:90%
need to worry about water.

00:17:14.740 --> 00:17:17.400 align:middle line:90%
So here is water close by.

00:17:17.400 --> 00:17:22.170 align:middle line:84%
But there are some different
paintings and different art

00:17:22.170 --> 00:17:26.250 align:middle line:84%
that they are using
to leave messages

00:17:26.250 --> 00:17:33.280 align:middle line:84%
for those who are coming
and for the next generation

00:17:33.280 --> 00:17:35.110 align:middle line:90%
